sections.Biography:
Ser Harys Sywft is the Knight of Cornfield and the head of House Swyft, a knightly house of [[the Westerlands]]. He's the father of [[Dorna Swyft]], the wife of Ser [[Kevan Lannister]]
===[[Season 1]]===
Ser Harys is present for a strategy meeting assembled by Lord [[Tywin Lannister]] following the defeat and capture of Ser [[Jaime Lannister]] in the [[Battle of the Whispering Wood]]. Also present are [[Tyrion Lannister]], Ser Kevan Lannister, Lord [[Leo Lefford]], Ser [[Addam Marbrand]], and [[Lannister bannerman 2 (The Ghost of Harrenhal)|another bannerman]], as well as Tywin's servants. Ser Harys remains quite while the other bannermen discuss their next move. When Tywin grows exasperated and dismisses the council, Ser Harys departs along with everyone present, except for Tyrion, whom Tywin orders to stay&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Fire and Blood]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
